The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 19 September is 3,281 (379.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 15 September, there were 102 new confirmed cases (11.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 September, there were 164 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 38% (62 fewer cases).
